        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 3:00PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 259 PM CDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm near Bowen, or 11 miles southeast of Carthage, moving
southeast at 30 mph. At 257 PM, a spotter in Bowen reported hail up
to the size of dimes.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could cause minor tree limb damage and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Augusta around 305 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
